MySQL: Key reads from disk
item.description: The number of physical reads of a key block from disk.

item.name: MySQL: key reads requests
item.description: The number of requests to read a key block from the cache.

item.name: MySQL: Qcache not cached
item.description: The number of noncached queries (not cacheable, or not cached due to the query_cache_type setting).

item.name: MySQL: Queries
item.description: The number of statements executed by the server. This variable includes statements executed within stored programs, unlike the Questions variable. It does not count COM_PING or COM_STATISTICS commands. This variable was added in MySQL 5.0.76.

item.name: MySQL: Query cache prunes per day
item.description: $mycalc{'query_cache_prunes_per_day'} mysqltunner

item.name: MySQL: query cache size
item.description: The number of noncached queries (not cacheable, or not cached due to the query_cache_type setting).

item.name: MySQL: Questions
item.description: The number of statements executed by the server. As of MySQL 5.0.72, this includes only statements sent to the server by clients and no longer includes statements executed within stored programs, unlike the Queries variable. This variable does not count COM_PING, COM_STATISTICS, COM_STMT_PREPARE, COM_STMT_CLOSE, or COM_STMT_RESET commands.

trigger.name: MySQL: Connections aborted - {ITEM.VALUE1}
trigger.description: Your applications are not closing MySQL connections properly

trigger.name: MySQL: Connection usage - {ITEM.VALUE1}
trigger.description: max_connections - increase wait_timeout - decrease interactive_timeout - decrease

trigger.name: MySQL: Enable the slow query log to troubleshoot bad queries
MySQL: Engine BDB is enabled but isn't being used
trigger.description: Add skip-bdb to MySQL configuration to disable BDB

trigger.name: MySQL: Engine InnoDB is enabled but isn't being used
trigger.description: Add skip-innodb to MySQL configuration to disable InnoDB

trigger.name: MySQL: Engine ISAM is enabled but isn't being used
trigger.description: Add skip-isam to MySQL configuration to disable ISAM (MySQL > 4.1.0)

trigger.expression: {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.innodb_buffer_pool_size.last()} < {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.engine.InnoDB.size.last()} and {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.pct_physical_memory.last()}<80 and {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.Uptime.last()} > 24h

MySQL: Increasing the query_cache size over 128M may reduce performance
trigger.description: mysqltuner

trigger.name: MySQL: InnoDB log waits - {ITEM.VALUE1}
trigger.description: Increase 'innodb_log_buffer_size'.

trigger.name: MySQL: Joins performed without indexes - {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Increase 'join_buffer_size' or always use indexes with joins

trigger.name: MySQL: Lack of available qcache memory

trigger.description: Increase 'open_files_limit'

dependency.name: MySQL: MySQL's maximum memory usage is dangerously high

trigger.name: MySQL: Sorts requiring temporary tables - {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Increase 'sort_buffer_size' and 'read_rnd_buffer_size'

trigger.name: MySQL: Table cache hit rate {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Increase 'table_open_cache' gradually to avoid file descriptor limits Read this before increasing 'table_open_cache' over 64: http://bit.ly/1mi7c4C

trigger.name: MySQL: Table locks acquired immediately - {ITEM.VALUE1}
trigger.description: Optimize queries and/or use InnoDB to reduce lock wait

trigger.name: MySQL: Temporary tables created on disk {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Temporary table size is already large - reduce result set size Reduce your SELECT DISTINCT queries without LIMIT clauses

trigger.expression: {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.pct_temp_disk.last()}>27 and {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.max_tmp_table_size.last()}<256M and {Template App MySQL:script.mysql.Uptime.last()}>1d
trigger.name: MySQL: Temporary tables created on disk {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Increase 'tmp_table_size' Increase 'max_heap_table_size' When making adjustments, make tmp_table_size/max_heap_table_size equal Reduce your SELECT DISTINCT queries without LIMIT clauses

trigger.name: MySQL: Thread cache hit rate - {ITEM.VALUE1}
trigger.description: Increase 'thread_cache_size'

trigger.name: MySQL: Thread cache is disabled
trigger.description: Set 'thread_cache_size' to 4 as a starting value

trigger.name: MySQL: Too many query_cache_prunes_per_day - {ITEM.VALUE1}.
trigger.description: Increase query_cache_size
